<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="151" type="reference_group">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo pratensis" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis">Tenthredo pratensis</taxonomicName>
Linnaeus, 1758: 556. Sex not given. Syntypes (assumed). Lectotype ♀ designated by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933408654888" author="Malaise, R" journalOrPublisher="Zoologischer Anzeiger" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" refId="B128" refString="Malaise, R, Benson, RB, 1934. The Linnean Types of Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Arkiv foer Zoologi 26(4 [A20]): 1-14. https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933408654888" title="The Linnean Types of Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta). Arkiv foer Zoologi 26 (4 [A 20]): 1 - 14." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933408654888" year="1934">Malaise and Benson (1934)</bibRefCitation>
. Type locality: Europe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="151">
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tenthredinidae" genus="Tenthredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tenthredo (Dolerus) deserta" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="151" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="deserta" subGenus="Dolerus">Tenthredo (Dolerus) deserta</taxonomicName>
Klug, 1818: 300-301. ♂. Holotype. Published type locality: &quot;In hiesiger Gegend gefunden&quot; [meaning the environs of Berlin, Germany].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
